                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="505.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Matter exists in four physical states: solid, liquid, gas, and plasma. Solids have a definite shape and volume due to tightly packed particles vibrating in place. Liquids maintain a definite volume but take the shape of their container, as particles slide past one another. Gases have neither a definite shape nor volume, allowing them to spread freely. Plasma, found in stars and lightning, consists of highly energized, charged particles." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="626.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Matter is classified based on composition into pure substances and mixtures. Pure substances include elements and compounds with uniform and definite compositions. Elements are made up of only one kind of atom, while compounds consist of two or more elements chemically bonded together. Mixtures are physical combinations of substances and may be homogeneous (uniform, like saltwater) or heterogeneous (non-uniform, like a salad)." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="744.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Physical properties of matter can be observed without changing its identity. These include color, odor, melting point, boiling point, density, and solubility. Chemical properties, in contrast, describe how a substance reacts with other substances, such as flammability or the ability to rust. Observing a chemical property usually involves a chemical change that alters the substanceâ€™s composition." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="1131.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Matter can undergo physical or chemical changes. Physical changes affect only the appearance or state of a substance without altering its composition (e.g., melting ice). Chemical changes result in the formation of new substances with different properties, such as when wood burns or iron rusts. Recognizing these changes is essential in identifying and understanding chemical processes." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
